HUMBLE.Definition: not proud or not believing that you are important

ROOTS.Definition: family origins, or the particular place you come from and the experiences you have had living there

OUTNUMBERING.Definition: to be greater in number than someone or something

WANDERING.Definition: to walk around slowly in a relaxed way or without any clear purpose or direction

SHOVELED.Definition: to put large quantities of food into your mouth very quickly

INDUSTRIALISATION.Definition: the process of developing industries in a country

ASSERTED.Definition: to behave in a way that expresses your confidence, importance, or power and earns you respect from others

ANCESTOR.Definition: someone or something related to you who lived a long time ago

FORAGING.Definition: to go from place to place searching for things that you can eat or use

PREDATORS.Definition: an animal that hunts, kills, and eats other animals

BRANCHES.Definition: one of the parts of a tree that grows out from the main trunk and has leaves, flowers, or fruit on it

REMAINS.Definition: a person's or animal’s remains are what is left of their dead body

GRAIN.Definition: a seed or seeds from a plant, especially a plant like a grass such as rice or wheat

LAY.Definition: (of an animal or bird) to produce eggs from out of the body

FATE.Definition: what happens to a particular person or thing, especially something final or negative, such as death or defeat

SEALED.Definition: if an action, event, or situation seals your fate, nothing can stop some unpleasant thing happening to you

ARTIFICIAL.Definition: made by people, often as a copy of something natural

INCUBATION.Definition: the process in which a bird, etc. keeps its eggs warm until the young come out, or the process in which an egg develops until the stage at which the young come out

HATCH.Definition: to (cause an egg to) break in order to allow a young animal to come out

DELICACY.Definition: something especially rare or expensive that is good to eat

FATTEN UP.Definition: to give an animal or a thin person a lot of food so that they become fatter

WHEAT.Definition: a plant whose yellowish-brown grain is used for making flour, or the grain itself

TENDED.Definition: to be likely to behave in a particular way or have a particular characteristic

GUINEA FOWL.Definition: a large grey and white African bird, kept for its eggs and meat

ERA.Definition: a period of time of which particular events or stages of development are typical

ANTIBIOTICS.Definition: a medicine or chemical that can destroy harmful bacteria in the body or limit their growth

RAISED.Definition: to take care of a person, or an animal or plant, until they are completely grown

HABITAT.Definition: the natural environment in which an animal or plant usually lives

CONFINED.Definition: to keep someone or something closed in a place, often by force

MORAL.Definition: relating to the standards of good or bad behaviour, fairness, honesty, etc. that each person believes in, rather than to laws

PROTEIN.Definition: one of the many substances found in food such as meat, cheese, fish, or eggs, that is necessary for the body to grow and be strong

REFLECTIVE.Definition: if something reflects something else, it shows that it is affected by it and is adjusted accordingly

AFFORDABILITY.Definition: the state of being cheap enough for people to be able to buy

BLAND.Definition: not having a strong taste or character or not showing any interest or energy

SHEER.Definition: used to emphasize how very great, important, or powerful a quality or feeling is; nothing except

WIPED OUT.Definition: to destroy something completely or cause something to be completely lost

ERASED.Definition: to remove or destroy something, especially something that shows that that person or thing ever existed or happened

PUZZLED.Definition: a situation that is difficult to understand

RETREAT.Definition: to go away from a place or person in order to escape from fighting or danger

DRAWS IN.Definition: if days, evenings, or nights draw in, it becomes darker earlier because autumn or winter is coming

‍TWIST OF FATE.Definition: if something happens by a twist of fate, it happens by chance, and it is strange, interesting, or unfortunate in some way

‍ERODED.Definition: to slowly reduce or destroy something

‍PATCH.Definition: a small area that is different in some way from the area that surrounds it
